\pard\plain \tx720\ri-16872\ql\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 When considering food, whether it is categorised as fruit or vegetable depends on assuming a botanical or culinary perspective. The botanical }{\f0\fs24 classification is based on the structure and function of the part of the plant in question, whereas the culinary classification takes flavour and structure as its primary characteristics for classification. As a result tomatoes, cucumber and green beans are considered vegetables by a cook whilst these are considered fruits according to botanical discipline. Assume }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 two ontologies B(otany) and C(ulinary), each specifying the semantics ascribed to their particular data as depicted in \\cref\{fig:alignment-a\}}{\f0\fs24  }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0    }
